        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/46827",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=croensch",
                        "name": "croensch",
                        "displayName": "Christoph Roensch",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Back then i just used a urlencode() around my parameter. Is this the same quoting as described in the RFC for the [Internet Message Format|http:\/\/tools.ietf.org\/html\/rfc5322#section-3.2.3], or do we have to implement something else?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=croensch",
                        "name": "croensch",
                        "displayName": "Christoph Roensch",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-05-27T02:37:26.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-05-27T02:37:26.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49015",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Is this still an issue?  I wasn't able to reproduce the result you describe when including a comma in the second argument of {{setFrom}} or {{add*}} methods.  This is the test that I used:\r\n{code}\r\n\/**\r\n * @group ZF-10792\r\n *\/\r\npublic function testCommaInRecipientNameIsEncodedProperly()\r\n{\r\n    $mail = new Zend_Mail();\r\n    $mail->setFrom('test@test.com', 'Test, Test');\r\n    $mail->addTo('adam@lundrigan.ca', 'Doe, John');\r\n    $mail->setBodyText('foo');\r\n    $mail->send();\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\nThe email was delivered to my mail server with the correct recipients and display names intact. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-11-08T12:03:21.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-11-08T12:03:21.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49055",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=croensch",
                        "name": "croensch",
                        "displayName": "Christoph Roensch",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I have to add that this bug only occured on linux servers wich mail() to a local sendmail before it goes to the \"Exchange\", MS Exchange in that case. Maybe that is part of the problem, i'll try it out tomorrow.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=croensch",
                        "name": "croensch",
                        "displayName": "Christoph Roensch",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-11-10T19:45:35.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-11-10T19:45:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49129",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=croensch",
                        "name": "croensch",
                        "displayName": "Christoph Roensch",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Well without umlauts this works as expected!\r\n\r\nZend_Mail::getHeader() reports:\r\n{code}\"Doe, John\" <john.doe@example.org>{code}\r\n\r\nHowever with umlauts, when i take \"D\u00f6e, John\" as name, Zend_Mail::getHeader() reports:\r\n{code}=?UTF-8?Q?D=C3=B6e, =20John?= <john.doe@example.org>{code}\r\nSending it from Windows to our SMTP works fine. Header unchanged.\r\n\r\nWhen the nullmailer in Ubuntu handles this, the header in the Outlook Message Options reads like this:\r\n{code}<=?UTF-8?Q?D=C3=B6e@localhost>, =20John?= <john.doe@example.org>{code}\r\n\r\nSo nullmailer thinks it got 2 adresses here, i don't know.\r\n* Is the display name supposed to be not \"quoted\" when it is UTF-8?\r\n* Isn't the comma a special character to seperate adresses and therefor needed to be escaped by any means?\r\n\r\nIf i pass \"D\u00f6e%2C John\" it works just fine again:\r\n{code}=?UTF-8?Q?D=C3=B6e%2C=20John?= <john.doe@example.org>{code}\r\nBut now the space has changed to =20 by nullmailer!?\r\n\r\nMy advice is to ditch nullmailer and use SMTP directly from Zend_Mail. Thats is the cool thing about this component.\r\nIf anyone could figure out the RFC and tell us when and how to escape stuff it would be even better.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=croensch",
                        "name": "croensch",
                        "displayName": "Christoph Roensch",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-11-17T16:34:07.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-11-17T16:34:07.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49134",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=croensch",
                        "name": "croensch",
                        "displayName": "Christoph Roensch",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I think i found where it should be encoded.\nThis patch will add the comma to Zend_Mime::encodeQuotedPrintable(), i also added two assertions in Zend_MailTest.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=croensch",
                        "name": "croensch",
                        "displayName": "Christoph Roensch",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-11-18T09:02:32.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-11-18T09:02:32.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51095",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Fixed in svn r24953.",
